The paper deals with convolutional codes and their properties when streaming over a network with link failures. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also introduces a new family of convolutional codes, which could potentially fall under coding theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of matrices in the construction of these codes could also relate to linear algebra (cs.LA) and scientific computing (cs.SC). Finally, the paper discusses the error correction capability of the codes, which could fall under the category of coding and information theory (cs.CC).
